      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm a DEI consultant and I've got a really tough meeting coming up with some old-school executives who are basically totally against our new diversity initiatives. They think the whole thing is a waste of time or even discriminatory. Can you help me prep? I need you to play devil's advocate and give me the strongest, most logical arguments against affirmative action and DEI. Like, don't give me the \"fluff\" or \"safe\" answers—I need to hear what their actual stance is so I can respond to it properly. Focus on the meritocracy argument and why they think race-conscious policies are actually unfair.",
